                <h1>Celebrate Joy: Understanding the 4th Sunday of Lent</h1>
                <p>The 4th Sunday of Lent, also known as Laetare Sunday, marks a mid-point in the Lenten season. It’s a day of joy amidst reflection, symbolized by the rose-colored vestments worn in churches. This Sunday encourages believers to rejoice in the hope of Easter, signifying a time for renewal and the anticipation of Christ’s resurrection.</p>
